fields.Title: WHIRLING F1 / SPARE WORKSHOP KEYS
fields.Condition: CheckItem("key_workshop_spare") == false  and  Variable["whirling.sense_hardie_window_clicked"]  and  Variable["TASK.enter_cavern_done"] == false  and  IsHourBetween(7, 22) == true
fields.Description: Somewhere in the room are the previous owner's spare keys to the pinball workshop (door in kitchen). This is the (perc check hidden) dialogue where you find them. (One path to hidden access to roof)1) Mis-connect to instigator because of room

fields.Title: Alain: ""What the fuck does the kitchen hav..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What the fuck does the kitchen have to do with this?" The tattooed man does not understand.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "It's close enough to the latch up t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's close enough to the latch up there -- one can slide it open and just take it. Surely not a coincidence.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""It's an older building -- who know..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's an older building -- who knows?" He shrugs.

fields.Title: Empathy: "It's said without aggression -- as..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's said without aggression -- as genuine advice.

fields.Title: You: ""There's something out there.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "There's something out there."

fields.Title: Shanky: ""Yeah -- your mother.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah -- your mother."

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Nothing, as before. Just black bran..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Nothing, as before. Just black branches.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "You see two, maybe three bushes, gr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You see two, maybe three bushes, grown into a single thicket -- over a period of circa 50 years. It takes time for a hedge like that to form.

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "It's not a very good mother-joke, b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's not a very good mother-joke, but the room still laughs. Something about those mother-jokes just *works*.

fields.Title: Theo: ""Off yourself -- make it up to me,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Off yourself -- make it up to me, cop. I still got my money on that."

fields.Title: You: ""I need your guys to hand the key t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I need your guys to hand the key to me."

fields.Title: You: "Take the key."
fields.Dialogue Text: Take the key.

fields.Title: Empathy: "The shrug is disingenuous. He's int..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The shrug is disingenuous. He's intrigued -- if only for a moment.

fields.Title: Cafeteria Window: "There's a little slide panel up the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There's a little slide panel up there, to let some air in. No need to open it in spring. It's still too cold outside.

fields.Title: Glen: ""Why did she put it *back*? After s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why did she put it *back*? After she took it?"

fields.Title: Glen: ""Boss, I don't want to make excuses..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Boss, I don't want to make excuses for her, but..." He stops.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "There's a yellow ribbon tied to one..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There's a yellow ribbon tied to one of the branches -- light yellow, faded with time. A tiny splash of colour in the blackness of the thicket. Hanging from it -- a bronze key.

fields.Title: You: "(Look at the key in your hand.) "I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Look at the key in your hand.) "I wonder what doors does it open?"

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The kitchen -- the only part of the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The kitchen -- the only part of the building you haven't thoroughly searched yet.

fields.Title: Theo: "With a loud thud the old man stands..."
fields.Dialogue Text: With a loud thud the old man stands up -- pushes the window open -- grabs the key from the hawthorn branch and slides it across the table to you.

fields.Title: Theo: ""I'm tired of listening to your shi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm tired of listening to your shit."

fields.Title: Shanky: ""Wow, no. I hadn't heard that.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wow, no. I hadn't heard that."

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: Logic: "It's worth a try."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's worth a try.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""It's an older building -- who know..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's an older building -- who knows?" He shrugs.

fields.Title: You: ""Thank you." (Nod to the old man.)"
fields.Dialogue Text: "Thank you." (Nod to the old man.)

fields.Title: You: "Look out the window."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look out the window.
fields.tooltip6: A bird flew by. Wing beats.
fields.tooltip7: You've been here for a long time.

fields.Title: You: "[Revert your gaze.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Revert your gaze.]

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""There was a barred door on the roo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There was a barred door on the roof that did *not* have a lock -- perhaps there is one *downstairs* that does?" He looks around. "We should search the *kitchen*."

fields.Title: Alain: ""I think he's trying to find dirt o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I think he's trying to find dirt on us, in our box. It's what they do, Shanks. Did you know policemen are sometimes called *pigs*?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Didn't even know it was there..."..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Didn't even know it was there..." The man looks at the key in your hand -- then around the room. "Boys?"

fields.Title: Glen: ""Sorry, Fucko! These *guys* won't h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sorry, Fucko! These *guys* won't help you. Looks like you're gonna have to go bush-diving. The hawthorn's got a bitch of a bite!"

fields.Title: Theo: ""Don't thank me." The old man takes..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Don't thank me." The old man takes out his pack of chewing tobacco. "I don't give two shits about your key."

fields.Title: Cafeteria Window: "Behind the dockworkers: a ceiling h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Behind the dockworkers: a ceiling height window. The hawthorn branches scrape the glass like bony fingers.

fields.Title: Empathy: "The shrug is disingenuous. He's int..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The shrug is disingenuous. He's intrigued -- if only for a moment.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""A little wisdom from old Titus --..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "A little wisdom from old Titus -- not everything is connected to one thing. Keys just lie around. It's a messy world."

fields.Title: You: ""Maybe this is somehow connected to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Maybe this is somehow connected to Ruby getting to the roof?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It's for the blue door in the kitc..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's for the blue door in the kitchen -- the note inside said the workshop key is behind the window. This is that key." He makes a note in his blue notebook.

fields.Title: Alain: ""Yeah -- because they like to sniff..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah -- because they like to sniff around in *dirt*." The tattooed man gives you a look.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Wild theory, cop-man. The worst th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wild theory, cop-man. The worst thing is -- I like it. She's been in this box plenty of times. This would give her access to the workshop route."

fields.Title: Logic: "He's just trying to sound clever. H..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's just trying to sound clever. He has no idea what you're looking for -- nor do you, yourself.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "The men are talking, but you swear..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The men are talking, but you swear you hear those black limbs tap on the window as the wind blows outside.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Nothing. Just black tangles like th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Nothing. Just black tangles like the hair of an old woman. Motionless. The wind in the yard doesn't reach the hawthorn, nor does the light come in from this window.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Huh?" The big guy looks behind him..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Huh?" The big guy looks behind him.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "It wasn't time yet. You have to kno..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It wasn't time yet. You have to know of the girl... Return when you know more.

fields.Title: Shanky: ""While you're in there -- make fatt..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "While you're in there -- make fatty a snack." He grins. "Can't you hear how his stomach is growling?!"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""It's a solid point, Shanks. There'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's a solid point, Shanks. There's a lot of things off about pinning this on Ruby. Be careful when you find her, cop -- be *fair*. Give her a chance to defend herself."

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Nothing, as always. By now you're a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Nothing, as always. By now you're almost certain there may be a sparrow's nest on one of the branches.

fields.Title: Shanky: ""I'm gonna enjoy the sight of you i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm gonna enjoy the sight of you in the bushes out there..."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""It's an older building -- who know..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's an older building -- who knows?" He shrugs.

fields.Title: Perception (Hearing): "You can and it's pretty terrifying."
fields.Dialogue Text: You can and it's pretty terrifying.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It's for the blue door in the kitc..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's for the blue door in the kitchen. There was a note there that you missed. It said the workshop key is behind the window. It's this key." He makes a note in his blue notebook.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Your secret route theory?" He shak..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Your secret route theory?" He shakes his head. "You're grasping for straws, cop-man. Why'd she put it back if it's hers?"

fields.Title: Shanky: ""What's this weirdo cop doing now,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What's this weirdo cop doing now, huh? Window-shopping?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""I'm not your janitor, cop." He gla..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm not your janitor, cop." He glances at the window. "I don't even know what you're talking about. There's nothing there."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""It's an older building -- who know..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's an older building -- who knows?" He shrugs.

fields.Title: You: ""Someone's hid a key in the bush."..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Someone's hid a key in the bush." (Point at the window.)

fields.Title: Cafeteria Window: "Again you find yourself looking at..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Again you find yourself looking at that big old window...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It *could* open the door in the ki..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It *could* open the door in the kitchen -- the blue door." He looks at the key in your hand. "It says 'Workshop, Spare' -- maybe there's a workshop there?"

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Yes. The nest of a common house spa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes. The nest of a common house sparrow. Passer domesticus.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""If he says it's there, it's there...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "If he says it's there, it's there." The lieutenant takes his glasses off to clean them -- then puts them back on.

fields.Title: You: ""Can you let me slide by so I can g..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Can you let me slide by so I can grab the thing?"

fields.Title: Theo: "The key is brass. 'Workshop, Spare'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The key is brass. 'Workshop, Spare' is etched into its bow. The old man closes the window and sits back down in silence.

fields.Title: Fat Angus: ""That's not even funny, Dennis.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's not even funny, Dennis."

fields.Title: Logic: "Someone hid the key in the bush and..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Someone hid the key in the bush and attached a yellow ribbon to make it easier to find.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Nothing. Even though you *know* you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Nothing. Even though you *know* you should see it -- you don't. Just branches like black tangles of hair. Motionless. The wind in the yard doesn't reach the hawthorn. Maybe come back later and you can try again?

fields.Title: You: "Look out the window."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look out the window.
fields.tooltip6: A bird flew by. Wing beats.
fields.tooltip7: You've been here for a long time.

fields.Title: Empathy: "It's said without aggression. In go..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's said without aggression. In good trust.

fields.Title: Alain: ""I don't know about that..." The ta..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't know about that..." The tattooed man yawns and settles more comfortably on the bench. "I'm comfortable here... don't think any sliding would really help right now."

fields.Title: You: ""Titus, can you hand the key to me..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Titus, can you hand the key to me please?"

fields.Title: Fat Angus: ""Goddamnit, Dennis. You know I can'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Goddamnit, Dennis. You know I can't help it!" His whiny voice is in deep contrast with his stature.

fields.Title: You: ""Does anyone know why this key was..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Does anyone know why this key was hanging right outside the Union box window?"

fields.Title: You: "Squint."
fields.Dialogue Text: Squint.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Keep at it. There must be a reason..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Keep at it. There must be a reason you've looked out this window so many times.

fields.Title: Alain: ""No idea.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No idea."

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "One can't see into the Union box fr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: One can't see into the Union box from the yard *outside* -- that hawthorn is too thick.

fields.Title: You: ""Maybe this is how Ruby got to the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Maybe this is how Ruby got to the roof that night? Using this key."

fields.Title: Glen: ""C'mon, man. We were just having so..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "C'mon, man. We were just having some fun! Where's the harm in...?"

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "You're not so sure about that. Some..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You're not so sure about that. Somehow you just *know* -- there's something out there, behind the glass.

fields.Title: Shanky: ""And *I* need the fatty to get his..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "And *I* need the fatty to get his feet amputated 'cause the smell is killing me -- we can't always get what we want."

fields.Title: Eugene: ""Never even seen it. Someone must h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Never even seen it. Someone must have hidden it there before this room became our place."

fields.Title: Glen: ""Sorry, Fucko! Looks like you're go..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sorry, Fucko! Looks like you're gonna have to go bush-diving. Good fucking luck with that -- the hawthorn's got a bitch of a bite!"

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The kitchen -- the only part of the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The kitchen -- the only part of the building you haven't thoroughly searched yet. It's worth a try!

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It says... 'Workshop, Spare'." He..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It says... 'Workshop, Spare'." He looks at the key in your hand. "There's a door in the *kitchen* that caught my eye yesterday -- it's very *blue*. Maybe there's a workshop behind it?"

fields.Title: Shanky: ""Look at Glenny and his girlfriend!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Look at Glenny and his girlfriend!"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Go ahead, Glen.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Go ahead, Glen."

fields.Title: Authority: "There is a silence around this man'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There is a silence around this man's words -- unlike Titus, they're *afraid* of him. That's the type of respect he commands.
